SIMPLE: mil
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mil
<hw>mil</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an obsolete monetary unit of
Cyprus equal in value to ⟦frac1x1000⟧ of a pound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a unit of length equal to ⟦frac1x1000⟧ inch, used
especially in measuring the thickness of sheets of materials.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>one milliliter; -- used mostly in informal
speech.</def> <mark>[laboratory slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> milliliter, millilitre, ml, cubic centimeter, cubic
centimetre, cc.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>a unit of angular size equal to ⟦frac1x6400⟧ of 360
degrees; -- it is used especially in artillery ranging.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mil.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mil</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: mil
<hw>mil</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[by contraction from
<ets>million</ets>.]</ety> <def>One million dollars; <as>as, his new
house cost over a <ex>mil</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Milady</ent>⟦br⟧
